<1ST_LINE>r a PM-NewAPBureau     11-07 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-New AP Bureau,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>New Bureau Opened In Northern Michigan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TRAVERSE CITY, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press has opened a
bureau in this northern Michigan city and appointed Paige St. John
as its first correspondent.
   Henry Ackerman, AP chief of bureau in Detroit, announced the
opening of the new Traverse City office Monday. It is the fourth AP
bureau in Michigan and the 142nd in the United States.
   Ms. St. John, 27, has been a newswoman in AP's Charleston, W.Va.,
bureau since joining the news cooperative in 1985. She is a native
of Limestone, Maine, and a graduate of Southern Illinois University.
   Before joining the AP, she worked on weekly newspapers in
Illinois and Tennessee. In 1987, she received the John M. Dougherty
Award, which is presented annually by the Associated Press Managing
Editors association for outstanding work by a young AP writer.
</TEXT>
