<TEXT>
   For Dennis Quaid, one of Hollywood's busiest
actors, much of his work in a movie comes before a single frame is
shot.
   To portray an astronaut, he learned to fly; to play a cop, he
spent a month on patrol; and to play rock legend Jerry Lee Lewis in
a forthcoming movie, he has spent months steeped in Lewis' life. He
even turned his living room into an impromptu recording studio.
   ``I'll sound like Jerry Lee Lewis if I can get inside of him,''
Quaid said in an interview published Sunday in The New York Times
Magazine.
