<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--DeerDeaths     11-07 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Deer Deaths,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Panicked Deer Killed When Jump Off Bridge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GLENMONT, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five deer that apparently were panicked by
hunters died after leaping off a New York Thruway bridge and landing
on the pavement of a highway 30 feet below.
   Four deer died immediately Sunday and had broken backs, said Ward
Stone, a New York state wildlife pathologist. A fifth deer suffering
internal injuries and a broken leg was shot by a police officer.
   Two other deer managed to escape into the surrounding forest in
the Albany area, but Stone said they probably suffered serious
injuries.
   ``If they had landed on soft earth, it would have been a whole
different ball game,'' Stone said.
   Stone said he expects such incidents to become more common as
suburbs encroached upon rural, wooded areas. ``I think society is
going to have this kind of problem increasingly,'' Stone said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
