<HEAD>Following material embargoed for 8:30 p.m. EST release</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Bush's blended snippets of biography, family tenderness and
praise from Reagan with a final taped appeal from the vice
president. ``Americans are better off that they were eight years
ago, and if you elect me president you will be better off four years
from now than you are today,'' he said.
   He paid tribute to his rival, but said he was a man without
experience in national security affairs.
   ``I can say that I believe I have the experience to be a steady
hand guiding our country,'' he said.
