<FILEID>AP-NR-11-07-88 0834EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Saudi-Oil     11-07 0126</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Saudi-Oil,0133</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Saudi Daily Production Reaches 6.4 Million Barrels</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Saudi Arabian oil production reached 6.4
million barrels a day during October, the Middle East Economic
Survey reported Monday.
   The respected oil newsletter said last month's production was up
from about 5 million barrels a day in September and 4.67 million
barrels a day in August.
   The Saudi Arabian production quota, set by the Organization o
Petroleum Exporting Countries, is 4.3 million barrels a day.
   But the Saudi Arabians are pumping extra oil in an effort to
force other OPEC members to cease exceding their own quotas.
   Overproduction has driven the price of oil in world markets down
by one third or more from the OPEC-set benchmark price of $18 a
barrel.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
