<2ND_LINE>BC-EEC-Steel,0091</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>EEC Steel Production Up 12.5 Percent In September</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Crude steel production in the 12-nation
European Economic Community rose 12.5 percent in September over a
year ago, a report released Monday by the EEC Commission found.
   However, the commission said that production dipped by 3.5
percent in September from August.
   The commission said production totaled 11.8 million metric tons
in the month of September. For the first nine months, production
totaled 101.6 million tons, up 8.5 percent from a year ago.
</TEXT>
