<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Fell 0.3 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production fell to 1.871 million tons in
the week ended Nov. 5, a decrease of 0.3 percent from the previous
week's 1.877 million tons, the American Iron and Steel Institute
reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 87.3 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 87.5 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
84.584 million net tons, a decrease of 15.1 percent from the 73.464
million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 89.2 percent of capacity,
compared with 77.4 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended Nov. 5: Northeast
Coast, 272,000; Pittsburgh, 189,000; Youngstown, 98,000; Lake Erie,
140,000; Detroit, 158,000; Chicago, 500,000; Midwest, 191,000;
Southern, 229,000; and Western, 94,000.
</TEXT>
