<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Time-Italy     11-07 0186</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Time-Italy,0194</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Time Inc. in Joint Venture To Publish Italian Fortune</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Time Inc. said Monday it has agreed tentatively
on a joint venture with the Italian magazine publisher Arnoldo
Mondadori Editore to publish an Italian edition of Fortune magazine.
   It would be the second such joint venture involving a
foreign-language edition of Fortune in Europe. Fortune France was
launched in February as a joint venture of Time and Hachette
Filipacchi, the Paris-based publisher.
   In the latest deal, Time and Arnoldo Mondadori said they would
each have a half-interest in the venture, which was expected to
produce its first monthly issue in early 1989 with an initial
circulation of about 50,000.
   Time said an editorial staff based in Milan, Italy, would produce
articles specifically for the magazine as well as draw on
translations or adaptations of articles from Fortune's
English-language editions.
   Time said it would continue distributing the biweekly
English-language Fortune International in Italy.
   Time Inc. and its affiliates publish 27 magazines, including
Time, Life, Money, People and Sports Illustrated. Arnoldo Mondadori
Editore publishes 23 magazines, including Panorama, Grazia, Epoca
and Espansione.
</TEXT>
