<HEAD>Polaroid-Shamrock Meeting Fails To Settle Dispute</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMBRIDGE, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A meeting between Polaroid Corp. and
Shamrock Holdings Inc. failed to settle a legal dispute over
Shamrock's hostile takeover bid for the instant camera company,
Polaroid said Monday.
   The meeting Sunday explored a possible settlement but ``because
of fundamental differences between the parties, no agreement was
reached,'' Polaroid said in a brief statement. The company refused
to provide any details.
   Shamrock is suing Polaroid in Delaware Chancery Court seeking to
invalidate Polaroid's employee stock ownership plan, which would all
but block a takeover.
   Shamrock made a hostile $42-a-share offer for Polaroid in
September after the camera company rebuffed two unsolicited bids.
The offer values Polaroid at about $2.6 billion.
